What Is Plymouth
Plymouth is a graphical boot system for Linux that displays animated logos or progress bars during system startup and shutdown, masking technical boot logs

If You Havent Install It You Can Install Using
sudo dnf install plymouth
after you install
sudo nano /etc/default/grub
Add quiet rhgb inside the quotes.
GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX="quiet rhgb"
Regenerate Grub
sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg
Install A Theme
sudo dnf install plymouth-theme-spinner
sudo dracut -f
(Trinity sets the default theme to bgrt. This can be confirmed by running sudo plymouth-set-default-theme --list then sudo plymouth-set-default-theme theme-name sudo dracut -f)
You can install other plymouth theme

sudo dnf install plymouth-theme-charge

sudo dnf install plymouth-theme-fade-in

sudo dnf install plymouth-theme-script

sudo dnf install plymouth-theme-solar

sudo dnf install plymouth-theme-spinfinity
